      "## Why Saudi Arabia Is Becoming a Global Event Destination",
      "The transformation is no accident. Under [Vision 2030](/portfolio/vision-2030), the government has poured tens of billions into entertainment, tourism, and event infrastructure — and the results are everywhere. The General Entertainment Authority (GEA) has unlocked live performances and large-scale festivals. New giga-projects like NEOM, the Red Sea, Diriyah Gate, and Qiddiya are creating venues that simply did not exist before. And global confidence is rising fast, with the Kingdom preparing to host Expo 2030 in Riyadh and the 2034 FIFA World Cup.",
      "For event planners, this means three things. First, the bar for quality is now extremely high — Saudi audiences have attended [Riyadh Season](/locations/riyadh) and Jeddah Season and they expect world-class production. Second, demand has exploded, so the best venues and vendors book out months in advance. Third, there is enormous opportunity to create something genuinely unforgettable, because the settings — desert canyons, Red Sea islands, heritage palaces — are unlike anywhere else on the planet.",
      "[INSIGHT] Saudi Arabia's events and entertainment sector has grown faster in the last four years than in the previous twenty combined. The MICE market alone is projected to grow from roughly SAR 12 billion in 2026 to over SAR 50 billion by 2030.",
