      "## Understanding the Event Planning Process in Saudi Arabia",
      "Great events are not lucky. They follow a disciplined process, and in Saudi Arabia that process has a few local steps that catch out first-time planners. Here is the high-level journey every professional event follows:",
      "- **Define the objective.** Before anything else, decide what the event must achieve — a specific feeling, a business outcome, a brand statement. Every later decision flows from this.",
      "- **Set a realistic budget.** Build it around the objective, not the other way around, and always hold a 10–15% contingency.",
      "- **Choose the city and venue.** Location shapes cost, logistics, and atmosphere more than any other single decision.",
      "- **Secure permits early.** GEA permits for entertainment, plus venue and municipality approvals, must start weeks in advance.",
      "- **Design and produce.** Concept, stage, AV, lighting, décor, catering, and guest experience all come together here.",
