      "- **The right [event management company](/services/corporate-events) saves more than it costs** by protecting your budget, preventing mistakes, and elevating the result.",
      "## Frequently Asked Questions",
      "[Q] How much does it cost to plan an event in Saudi Arabia in 2026?",
      "[A] Costs range widely by type and scale. A polished corporate conference typically runs SAR 250,000–1,200,000, a corporate gala SAR 600,000–3,000,000, a luxury wedding in Riyadh or Jeddah SAR 1,500,000–5,000,000+, and a destination wedding in AlUla or the Red Sea SAR 2,500,000–8,000,000+. The biggest cost drivers are custom production, premium catering, and remote logistics. A planner can build an itemised budget for your specific brief.",
      "[Q] How far in advance should I start planning an event in Saudi Arabia?",
      "[A] For a large corporate event or wedding in Riyadh or Jeddah, start 8–12 months ahead to secure top venues and vendors. For destination events in AlUla, allow 12–18 months because of RCU approvals and remote logistics. GEA entertainment permits should be filed 4–8 weeks out (10–12 weeks for international artists).",
      "[Q] Do I need a GEA permit for my event?",
      "[A] You need a General Entertainment Authority (GEA) permit if your event includes live music, performers, or public entertainment. Private family gatherings and simple business meetings without entertainment usually do not. The process takes 4–8 weeks, and the most common reason for rejection is missing GEA licenses for the performers themselves.",
      "[Q] Which city is best for hosting a premium event in Saudi Arabia?",
      "[A] Riyadh is best for government, finance, corporate, and royal-scale events; Jeddah for coastal weddings and relaxed luxury; AlUla for destination weddings and spectacular cultural events; and Dammam for energy-sector and B2B events. Match the city to the message your event needs to send.",
      "[Q] What does an event management company actually do?",
      "[A] A full-service event management company handles strategy, budgeting, venue sourcing, permits, design and production, catering, guest and VIP management, on-site execution, and post-event reporting. The best firms also bring creative direction, preferred-vendor pricing, and the local knowledge needed to navigate GEA, RCU, and municipality requirements.",
      "[Q] Is it cheaper to plan an event myself instead of hiring a planner?",
      "[A] Usually not. Professional planners hold preferred-vendor rates, avoid costly mistakes like missed permit deadlines, and know exactly where to allocate spend for impact. For any event above a modest scale, a good planner typically saves more than their fee while delivering a noticeably better result.",
      "[Q] How much should I budget for food per guest?",
      "[A] High-end catering in Saudi Arabia ranges from roughly SAR 1,200 to SAR 3,500+ per person, depending on the menu, service style, and venue. For a 500-guest event at SAR 1,500 per head, catering alone is around SAR 750,000, before cakes and bespoke stations.",
      "[Q] Can you host outdoor events in Saudi Arabia year-round?",
      "[A] Not comfortably. The event season for outdoor and destination events runs from roughly October to March, when temperatures are pleasant (15–25°C in AlUla). Summer months regularly exceed 40°C, making outdoor events impractical. Always build a weather contingency into outdoor plans.",
      "[Q] What is the most common event planning mistake in Saudi Arabia?",
      "[A] Starting too late. Delayed venue bookings and last-minute GEA permit applications cause the majority of avoidable problems — fewer venue options, rush fees, and last-minute panic. The fix is simple: lock your venue and begin your permit process as early as possible.",
